Mrs Zululand finalist, Luisa Momberg, pictured on the lawns of the bowling greens, is busy in preparation for the pageant that takes place in September. She hosted a social Bowls Day and invited amateur, pro and casual players who wanted to enjoy a day  out in the Ladysmith winter sun. Momberg has been hard at work supporting local charities and community outreaches ahead of the crowning ceremony. The aim of the pageant is to help the women of Zululand increase their cultural awareness by embracing the beauty and respective cultures and diversities in South Africa. Momberg thanked everyone who has supported her.